	<div id="id253b" class="post">
		<h2 class="title"><span class="image-wrapper"><img height="47" alt="Risky business" width="231" class="title" src="../../../resources/net.databinder.components.RenderedLabel/e4704891"/><span class="title">Risky business</span></span></h2>
		<div class="byline"><span>
			<span>By <span class="alias">n8han</span>, <span>on September 27, 2006</span></span>
			<span id="id253c" class="tags">
					{&nbsp;<span><a href="../../../code/tag/programming/#selected-tag"><span>programming</span></a><span id="id253d">, </span></span><span><a href="../../../code/tag/rails/#selected-tag"><span>rails</span></a><span id="id253e">, </span></span><span><a href="../../../code/tag/wicket/#selected-tag"><span>wicket</span></a></span>&nbsp;}
			</span>
		</span></div>
		<div><p>I&#8217;m going to continue to steal matériel from Rails and apply it to Wicket. They don&#8217;t know this yet, but we&#8217;re all on the same anti-enterprise-windbag team. It&#8217;s all about making things better for programmers, and not burying good ideas in a sea of what-ifs.</p>


	<p>From <a href="http://www.xml-blog.com/articles/2006/09/15/railsconf-europe-notes-dave-thomas-keynote-on-risk">Dave Thomas Keynote on Risk</a>:</p>


	<ul>
	<li>Risk must be mitigated, it can never be eliminated</li>
		<li>Don’t let fear paralyze you </li>
		<li>If you can’t be with the one you love: you’re selling yourself short. Quit.</li>
		<li>But that’s risky! Yes! :) Embrace risk. Risk/Reward.</li>
		<li>Opposite of risk is not safety, it’s stagnation</li>
	</ul>


	<p>That last one is a good summary of <a href="/n8/articles/2006/09/07/getting-fired-for-buying-ibm">how people get fired for buying <span class="caps">IBM</span></a>.</p></div>
	</div>
